sections.Development:
* '''Before November 2005''': [[David Benioff]] and [[D.B. Weiss]] meet [[George R.R. Martin]] to discuss adapting the books for television. They pass a &quot;test&quot; by guessing the identity of [[Jon Snow]]'s mother.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Watch_the_Emmy_Panel Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''March 2006''': Benioff and Weiss pitch ''Game of Thrones'' to [[HBO]] and [[wikipedia:Showtime (TV channel)|Showtime]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Watch_the_Emmy_Panel Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 January 2007''': HBO options ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117957532.html?categoryid=14&amp;cs=1 Variety article]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/2007/01/17/ George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''31 May 2007''': David Benioff, D.B. Weiss and George R.R. Martin appear on the social networking site ''Second Life'' to talk about the potential TV series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/2007/05/31/ George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 November 2007''': The [[wikipedia:2007-2008 Writer's Guild of America strike|Writer's Guild of America strike]] begins, delaying work on ''Game of Thrones'' for its duration.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/27951.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 December 2007''': George R.R. Martin confirms that work on the series remains suspended due to the strike.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/27951.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 February 2008''': The WGA strike ends, allowing work on the script for ''Game of Thrones''&lt;nowiki&gt;'&lt;/nowiki&gt;s pilot to resume.
* '''13 June 2008''': George R.R. Martin confirms that a second draft of the pilot script has been submitted to HBO and that the BBC will be co-funding the project (BBC eventually did not get involved).&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/46002.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''9 September 2008''': HBO exercises its option and buys the television rights to ''A Song of Ice and Fire''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/51779.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Pilot pre-production==
* '''11 November 2008''': HBO orders a pilot for ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/58155.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''14 November 2008''': David Benioff and D.B. Weiss leave a message on the Westeros forums thanking fans for their support and asking for casting suggestions.&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/32275-hello-from-benioff-and-weiss/ Westeros.org forum]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''19 November 2008''': David Benioff and D.B. Weiss confirm that the ages of many of the younger characters will be increased for production reasons and that the series will employ mostly British accents.&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/32275-hello-from-benioff-and-weiss/page__st__40__p__1593863&amp;#entry1593863 Westeros.org forum]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 January 2009''': George R.R. Martin discusses the TV series and the complications of merchandising rights related to the series in a podcast interview with THAC0.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.thacopodcast.com/?p=23 THAC0 podcast]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 March 2009''': [[wikipedia:Ireland|Ireland]] is mooted as the filming location for the series in unconfirmed comments from the head of HBO's programming department.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/03/hbo-president-talks-game-of-thrones/]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''18 March 2009''': ''[[wikipedia:Highlander (TV series)|Highlander]]'' actor [[wikipedia:Adrian Paul|Adrian Paul]] expresses an interest in auditioning for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/03/adrian-paul-expresses-interest-in-thrones/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 April 2009''': [[wikipedia:Scotland|Scotland]] and [[wikipedia:Morocco|Morocco]] are being touted as filming locations as well as Ireland.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/04/possible-remote-shooting-locations-revealed/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 April 2009''': HBO confirms that filming will begin in October at the [[Paint Hall]] studio facility in [[wikipedia:Belfast|Belfast]], [[wikipedia:Northern Ireland|Northern Ireland]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/84893.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.northernireland.gov.uk/news/news-ofmdfm/news-ofmdfm-210409-hbo-to-film.htm Northern Ireland government press release]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/news/us-television-pilot-game-of-thrones-to-be-filmed-in-belfast-14276293.html The Belfast Telegraph]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/04/press-release-confirms-northern-ireland/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 May 2009''': [[Peter Dinklage]] is the first announced cast member for ''Game of Thrones''. It is confirmed that he will be playing [[Tyrion Lannister]]. [[Thomas McCarthy]] is confirmed as the director of the pilot episode.&lt;ref&gt;[http://web.archive.org/20090507215708/www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/television/news/e3i30b29365238b3652295a5a9e328518de The Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/05/first-cast-member-and-director-announced/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/86651.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''18 May 2009''': [[wikipedia:Holly Marie Combs|Holly Marie Combs]] is rumored as being considered for the role of [[Catelyn Stark]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/05/holly-marie-combs-as-catelyn-or-how-a-bunch-of-asoiaf-fans-found-out-imdb-is-user-editable/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; The producers confirm this is not the case.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/05/david-dan-confirm-what-we-already-know/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''21 May 2009''': Casting for the ''Game of Thrones'' pilot is underway by this point.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/05/auditions-are-underway/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''13 June 2009''': Nina Gold is confirmed as ''Game of Thrones''&lt;nowiki&gt;'&lt;/nowiki&gt;s casting director.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/06/casting-director-info-and-more/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''6 July 2009''': Reports on a number of high-profile American TV commentators and bloggers discussing the project.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/07/tv-critics-jumping-on-the-thrones-bandwagon/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''19 July 2009''': [[Sean Bean]], [[Mark Addy]], [[Kit Harington]], [[Jack Gleeson]] and [[Harry Lloyd]] are announced as having been cast in the roles of [[Eddard Stark]], [[Robert Baratheon]], [[Jon Snow]], [[Joffrey Baratheon]] and [[Viserys Targaryen]] respectively&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/95840.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/07/sean-bean-and-more-cast-in-pilot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''3 August 2009''': It is announced that [[Jennifer Ehle]] has been cast as Catelyn Stark.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/television/news/e3icaec2feffc977edcd7939413cf46b0d9 The Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/2009/08/03/ George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/08/jennifer-ehle-cast-as-catelyn/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''18 August 2009''': The ''Game of Thrones'' production office in Belfast is up and running by this time.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/08/pilot-set-to-begin-production-soon/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/2009/08/18/ George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''20 August 2009''': Seven additional casting announcements are made: [[Nikolaj Coster-Waldau]] as [[Jaime Lannister]], [[Tamzin Merchant]] as [[Daenerys Targaryen]], [[Richard Madden]] as [[Robb Stark]], [[Iain Glen]] as [[Jorah Mormont]], [[Alfie Allen]] as [[Theon Greyjoy]], [[Sophie Turner]] as [[Sansa Stark]] and [[Maisie Williams]] as [[Arya Stark]].
*'''1 September 2009''': It is announced that [[Lena Headey]] will be playing [[Cersei Lannister]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2009/09/game-of-thrones-hbo-.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/lena-headey-cast-as-cersei/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/106073.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''3 September 2009''': [[wikipedia:Garret Dillahunt|Garret Dillahunt]] is reported to be interested in a role in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/garret-dillahunt-interested-in-thrones/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''8 September 2009''': Australian actor Conan Stevens expresses an interest in auditioning for the series for the role of [[Gregor Clegane]] and rapidly gains fan support.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/7-ft-actor-rumored-to-be-auditioning-for-thrones/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''22 September 2009''': Set construction at the Paint Hall is underway by this time.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/thrones-sets-present-in-paint-hall/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''23 September 2009''': It is confirmed that [[Rory McCann]] has been cast in the role of [[Sandor Clegane]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bscreview.com/2009/09/rory-mccann-is-the-hound-in-a-game-of-thrones/ BSC Review]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/109392.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/mccann-casting-official/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''24 September 2009''': Casting of extras for the pilot begins.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/09/call-for-extras-goes-out/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''1 October 2009''': [[Bronson Webb]] announces on his website that he has been cast as [[Will]] in the pilot.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bronsonwebb.com/ Bronson Webb's website]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''5 October 2009''': [[Esme Bianco]] confirms on her website that she will be playing [[Ros]], a prostitute in [[King's Landing]], in the pilot episode.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.esmeforever.com/news.php?newsID=27 Esme Bianco's website]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/by-george-i-think-we-got-it/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/116814.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''13 October 2009''': [[Isaac Hempstead-Wright]] is cast as [[Bran Stark]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2009/10/game-of-thrones-hbo.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/bran-confirmed-more-clues-given/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/116399.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''17 October 2009''': [[Jason Momoa]] is cast as [[Khal Drogo]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/jason-momoa-as-drogo/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2009/10/game-of-thrones-hbo.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/117211.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''20 October 2009''': Aimee Richardson is cast in a non-speaking role as [[Myrcella Baratheon]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/myrcella-cast-may-be-pilot-only-though/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO announces that [[Jamie Campbell Bower]], [[Joseph Mawle]], [[Richard Ridings]], [[Ron Donachie]], [[Donald Sumpter]] and [[Ian McNeice]] have been cast as [[Waymar Royce]], [[Benjen Stark]], [[Gared]], [[Rodrik Cassel]], Maester [[Luwin]] and [[Illyrio Mopatis]] respectively.&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2009/10/game-of-thrones-hbo-1.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/hbo-confirms-remainder-of-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/115542.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/115821.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/116399.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/116814.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''21 October 2009''': ''TIME Magazine'' reports on the almost-unprecedented buzz around a series that has not even started filming yet.&lt;ref&gt;[http://tunedin.blogs.time.com/2009/10/21/game-of-thrones-your-nonexistent-hbo-series-update/ TIME Magazine]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''22 October 2009''': David Benioff and D.B. Weiss once again thank the fans for their casting suggestions and support.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/benioff-weiss-thank-the-fans/ Westeros.org forum]&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.Season 1 filming:
* '''23 July 2010''': Filming begins. The first scene to be shot is a conversation between Eddard and Cersei that is not in the books. Another scene shot on this day is a conversation between Eddard and Arya from Episode 104.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/7/23/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; The initial weeks of shooting concentrate on scenes in the [[Red Keep]] in [[King's Landing]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/7/29/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''28 July 2010''': George R.R. Martin announces that Roy Dotrice has had to withdraw from the production due to ill health. He will be replaced in the role of Grand Maester Pycelle by [[Julian Glover]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/168109.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; In the UK, cable and satellite broadcaster Sky buys the exclusive UK transmission rights to all HBO television shows in a five-year deal. ''Game of Thrones'' will be among its acquisitions.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/BSkyB_to_Broadcast_Game_of_Thrones_in_UK/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 July 2010''': It is confirmed that [[Charles Dance]] has been cast in the role of [[Tywin Lannister]]. Dance, a fan of the novels, was the first choice of Benioff and Weiss for the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/07/game-of-thrones-charles-dance.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Charles_Dance_Cast_as_Tywin_Lannister/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; A conversation between Eddard Stark and Grand Maester Pycelle from Episode 104 is shot today.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/7/29/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''30 July 2010''': A meeting of the King's [[small council]] is filmed. Bryan Cogman corrects the actors' pronunciation of the word 'maester'.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/7/30/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 August 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Mark Stanley]] will be playing the role of [[Grenn]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/170329.html?thread=10836313#t10836313 George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 August 2010''': Conan Stevens flies to Belfast to begin preparing for filming his role of Gregor Clegane in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/the-mountain-of-belfast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 August 2010''': Filming takes place at Ballymoney. Which scene is being filmed is unclear, but speculation is that it is the confrontation between Joffrey and Sansa against Arya and Mycah.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/day-nine-on-location-in-ballymoney/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; A scene where Viserys and Daenerys Targaryen ride with the Dothraki across a plain is also filmed&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/8/3/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''4 August 2010''': Peter Dinklage has arrived in Belfast by this time.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/filming-what-we-know-so-far/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 August 2010''': The ''Times of Malta'' confirms that ''Game of Thrones'' will shoot on the island for six weeks later in 2010.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20100805/local/sinbad-to-be-shot-here-for-sky1 Times of Malta]&lt;/ref&gt; Daenerys's entrance to [[Vaes Dothrak]] is filmed at Sandy Brae in Northern Ireland, with Bryan Cogman indicating that the name '[[Essos]]', not used yet in the books, may be used in the series to refer to the eastern continent.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/8/5/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 August 2010''': HBO reiterates that they plan to show ''Game of Thrones'' in Spring 2011, potentially as early as the start of March.&lt;ref&gt;[http://livefeed.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/08/game-of-thrones-to-premiere-in-spring.html The Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''9 August 2010''': [[Amrita Acharia]] is interviewed by a Norwegian newspaper about her role as [[Irri]] in ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/acharia-talks-thrones-in-norwegian-paper/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 August 2010''': HBO confirm that [[Dar Salim]] has been cast as [[Qotho]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/new-clues-from-grrm/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 August 2010''': Finn Jones and Conan Stevens undergo horse riding training in Northern Ireland.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/photo-riding-lessons-for-jones-and-stevens/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; George R.R. Martin also confirms that [[Elyes Gabel]] and [[Joe Dempsie]] have been cast as [[Jhogo]] and [[Grenn]] respectively.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/jhogo-and-gendry-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO later announces that Gabel's character's name has been changed to Rakharo to avoid confusion with Drogo.
* '''18 August 2010''': It is announced that [[Owen Teale]] has replaced Derek Halligan in the role of [[Alliser Thorne]]. No reason is given for the recasting.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/teale-replaces-halligan-as-alliser-thorne/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; Conan Stevens and Rory McCann rehearse for the fight scene between Gregor and Sandor Clegane at the Hand's tourney.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/day-24-filming-the-tourney/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''20 August 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms additional casting news: [[Lalor Roddy]] as an assassin, [[Simon Lowe]] as a wineseller, [[Mark Lewis Jones]] as [[Shagga]], [[Clive Mantle]] as [[Greatjon Umber]] and [[Susie Kelly]] as [[Masha Heddle]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/175191.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 August 2010''': HBO co-president Michael Lombardo discusses the process of commissioning ''Game of Thrones'' in an interview with ''Vanity Fair''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.vanityfair.com/online/oscars/2010/08/whats-the-key-to-hbos-emmy-success.html Vanity Fair interview]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 August 2010''': Filming of the Hand's Tourney sequence is completed.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/08/day-32-tourney-wrapped-winterfell-next/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 September 2010''': HBO confirms that musician [[Wilko Johnson]] has been cast as Ser [[Ilyn Payne]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/09/ilyn-payne-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; The scene where Eddard Stark and Robert Baratheon confront one another over Arya's chastisement of Joffrey is being filmed on this date.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/09/day-39-filming-in-ballycarry/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 September 2010''': HBO releases a [[Trailers|new trailer]], a behind-the-scenes video, a new promotional still of Emilia Clarke as Daenerys and begin a new production blog updating viewers on filming progress. Writer Bryan Cogman also begins releasing postdated production diaries on filming progress. Today a scene from Episode 102 where Eddard talks to Cersei is filmed.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/index.html HBO Game of Thrones website]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/ HBO production blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 September 2010''': Actress [[wikipedia:Tricia Helfer|Tricia Helfer]] reveals via Twitter that she auditioned for the role of Cersei Lannister.&lt;ref&gt;[https://twitter.com/trutriciahelfer/status/25332461684 Tricia Helfer's Twitter]&lt;/ref&gt; She also indicates that [[wikipedia:Elizabeth Banks|Elizabeth Banks]] may have also auditioned for the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/09/quick-hits-more-extras-helfer-auditions-and-ratings/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 September 2010''': By this day the focus of the filming has moved to Winterfell and interior shooting at the Paint Hall studio. Several scenes are filmed on this day focusing on the character of Bran Stark.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/9/23/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; Sources on the production claim that almost fifty different locations are being used in Northern Ireland for the shoot.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/09/day-60-filming-continues-at-castle-ward/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 September 2010''': HBO releases a new behind-the-scenes video focusing on set and prop design.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/9/27/the-artisans-gemma-jackson.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 September 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Art Parkinson]] will be playing [[Rickon Stark]] and that [[Mia Soteriou]] is playing [[Mirri Maz Duur]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/178461.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 October 2010''': HBO releaes a new production photograph, this time of the seat of the King's Hand at the small council meetings.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/10/1/latest-set-photo.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 October 2010''': George R.R. Martin reports that [[Ben Hawkey]] will be playing the role of [[Hot Pie]], while [[Lommy Greenhands]] will be played by [[Eros Vlahos]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/179706.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 October 2010''': Wilko Johnson's local newspaper reports about his role as Ser Ilyn Payne.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.echo-news.co.uk/news/local_news/castlepoint/8435080.Feelgoods____Wilko_to_star_as_TV_bad_guy/ Echo News]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''8 October 2010''': HBO releases a new video discussing the lift at Castle Black and how they built it for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/10/8/the-artisans-gemma-jackson-on-the-castle-black-lift.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''14 October 2010''': HBO confirms that [[Ian Beattie]] has been cast as Ser [[Meryn Trant]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/10/the-kingsguard-adds-a-knight/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; They also release a new promotional image of Jerome Flynn as Bronn.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/10/14/latest-photo.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''20 October 2010''': Filming of scenes in Winterfell and the Eyrie take place around this time, including scenes with Bran and Osha at Winterfell.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/10/day-90-filming-at-winterfell-and-the-eyrie/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 October 2010''': HBO confirms that composter [[Stephen Warbeck]] will be creating the original music for the show&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Exclusive_Game_of_Thrones_Composer/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''25 October 2010''': London-based visual effects company BlueBolt is confirmed as working on the project.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/10/quick-hits-vfx-company-added-dothraki-creator-interviewed/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''26 October 2010''': Peter Dinklage gives his first public comments on the project, talking about the relationship between Tyrion and Cersei and how he and Lena Headey, who are good friends, play it.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/10/26/lovehate-relationship.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 October 2010''': HBO release a new photo, this time of the mural on the wall of the King's Hand's bedchamber in the Red Keep.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/10/27/latest-photo-inside-the-red-keep.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; George R.R. Martin gives a very brief set report, indicating that the sets for the Eyrie and the Red Keep are very impressive.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/181418.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''28 October 2010''': Castmembers and fans of the books again mingle at a second 'moot' in Belfast. George R.R. Martin is in attendance, as are producer Bryan Cogman and a number of actors, including Luke McEwan, Kit Harington, Mark Addy, Kristian Nairn, Jamie Sives, Gethin Anthony, Finn Jones, Miltos Yerolemou and John Bradley-West.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/10/reports-from-the-2nd-annual-belfast-moot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; A Russian fan site posts a report on the reshooting of the wedding scene between Daenerys and Khal Drogo at Dwerja on Malta.&lt;ref&gt;[http://westeros.ru/?p=5892 Westeros.ru]&lt;/ref&gt; Lena Headey also reports that she is in Malta for the week to shoot a 'pivotal' scene,&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/10/day-98-malta-filming/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; later confirmed to be a notable execution scene.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/11/day-102-details-of-malta-filming ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 October 2010''': HBO release a new behind-the-scenes video about costume design in the show.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hbo.com/video/video.html?view=grid&amp;vid=1133489&amp;autoplay=true HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 November 2010''': It is revealed that [[wikipedia:Fort Ricasoli|Fort Ricasoli]] on Malta is standing in for the [[Red Keep]], whilst the village of Manikata has stood in for the Lhazareen village raided by Khal Drogo.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/11/day-102-details-of-malta-filming ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 November 2010''': HBO puts up a new blog entry about the interior design skills of the Night's Watch.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/2/home-is-where-the-raw-meat-is.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 November 2010''': HBO issue a full line-up of the directors for the first season and which episodes they are handling.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/11/game-of-thrones-director-line-up-revealed/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 November 2010''': HBO confirm the casting of [[Brian Fortune]], [[Stephen Don]] and [[Ian Gelder]] as [[Bowen Marsh]], [[Stiv]] and Ser [[Kevan Lannister]] respectively.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Three_Actors_Confirmed/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO also publishes a new blog entry revealing that the cast has held a full read-through of episodes 6-10 of the series in Belfast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/5/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms-read-through.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 November 2010''': Early reports that adult film star [[Sahara Knite]] will be playing a role in the series are confirmed, with the news that she will be playing a new character called [[Armeca]], an associate of Ros who works in the same brothel, an establishment owned by Littlefinger. This also confirms that Ros will appear in the series itself as well as the pilot.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/11/as-seen-on-tv-game-of-thrones-to-feature-many-new-scenes/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 November 2010''': Filming in Malta concludes.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/4626/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 November 2010''': It is revealed that [[Beric Dondarrion]] has been cast, with [[David Michael Scott]] playing the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''18 November 2010''': ''Entertainment Weekly'' publish ten new publicity images from the series on their website.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.ew.com/ew/gallery/0,,20385926_20442931,00.html Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''19 November 2010''': Mark Addy reports that he has wrapped his filming on the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/leisure/theatre/8676593.Charles_Hutchinson_previews_Mark_Addy_in_Kidstory_at_the_Theatre_Royal_Studio/ The York Theatre]&lt;/ref&gt; The production spurs controversy in Malta after reports of environmental damage caused by filming.&lt;ref&gt;[http://io9.com/5694571/filming-of-a-game-of-thrones-obliterated-the-ecosystem-on-a-protected-beach io9]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''20 November 2010''': HBO releases a new production photo highlighting props on the show, depicting a dagger and a book.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/20/latest-photo-dagger.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 November 2010''': HBO releases a new behind-the-scenes video highlighting the use of weapons and swords in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/22/the-artisans-tommy-dunne.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''24 November 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that actor [[David Bradley]] as been cast as Lord [[Walder Frey]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/184176.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO also confirms that [[Andrew Wilde]] has been cast as [[Tobho Mott]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/11/grrm-confirms-bradley-as-frey-we-add-one-more/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''26 November 2010''': HBO republishes high-definition versions of the pictures from ''Entertainment Weekly''&lt;nowiki&gt;'&lt;/nowiki&gt;s web and print coverage.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/26/high-resolution-ew-photos.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 November 2010''': HBO airs a promo for ''Inside Game of Thrones'', a fifteen-minute behind-the-scenes special, due to air on 5 December.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/27/inside-game-of-thrones-preview.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 November 2010''': HBO releases the [[Trailers|third teaser trailer]] for ''Game of Thrones'', this one 60 seconds in length and featuring an exchange of dialogue between Eddard and Bran Stark as well as other short clips.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/11/28/clip-preview.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 December 2010''': HBO publishes a new production blog entry in which they confirm that Maisie Williams, who is right-handed, is playing Arya as left-handed, as in the novels.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/12/1/dispatches-from-the-seven-kingdoms-the-favored-hand.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 December 2010''': HBO airs a ten-minute documentary entitled '''Making Game of Thrones''', featuring behind-the-scenes footage and a few new clips.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2010/12/5/inside-game-of-thrones-feature.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; A longer edition with several additional clips is also posted to YouTube.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-EVKp5nYxyI YouTube]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''6 December 2010''': HBO begins selling ''Game of Thrones'' merchandise through its online store, starting with T-shirts and the books.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/12/official-game-of-thrones-merchandise-now-available/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 December 2010''': Scenes filmed today include Tyrion and the mountain clans' arrival at Tywin Lannister's camp and their introduction to the Lannister high command.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/12/day-138-filming-winding-down/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 December 2010''': Rumors suggest that HBO is already scouting locations in Iceland and Morocco for a possible second season of the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/12/rumor-hbo-looking-at-iceland-and-morocco-for-season-two/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 December 2010''': This is the planned wrap date on Season 1 of ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Wrapping_Up_Season_One/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; Previous rumors had suggested the 18th as the wrap date.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/4626/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; The British ''Daily Express'' newspaper interviews Rory McCann about the series and he reveals that he was living rough in Iceland at the time he was cast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.dailyexpress.co.uk/posts/view/217539/My-career-was-on-Ice-but-now-I-m-back-says-Rory/ The Daily Express]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 December 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that shooting has wrapped.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/189065.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Post-Season 1 filming period==
* '''21 December 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that the episodes will have individual titles. His episode (episode 8) has the working title ''The Pointy End''. It is also revealed that the first three episodes are now edited and done.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/12/podcast-interview-with-grrm-reveals-some-new-info/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 January 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' is heavily featured on the TCA Winter Press Tour in the USA, with actors Sean Bean, Emilia Clarke and Peter Dinklage, producers David Benioff and D.B. Weiss and creator George R.R. Martin all attending.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/TCA_Winter_Press_Tour/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO confirm that '''Game of Thrones''' will begin airing on HBO on 17 April 2011.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/1/7/game-of-thrones-premiere-date-announced.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 January 2011''': Video interviews with Peter Dinklage, Emilia Clarke and Sean Bean are released.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/01/access-hollywood-interviews-thrones-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 January 2011''': HBO release a new behind-the-scenes video about the work of stuntmen in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/1/13/the-artisans-buster-reeves.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 January 2011''': HBO release a new promotional picture of the [[Iron Throne]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/1/16/latest-photo-the-iron-throne.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; and a [[Trailers|new trailer]], entitled 'Thrones', showing major castmembers sitting on the [[Iron Throne]] accompanied by lines of dialogue from the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/1/16/iron-throne-preview.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''20 January 2011''': George R.R. Martin and the producers confirm that the sexuality of the gay characters from the books will be more prominent in the TV series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.afterelton.com/tv/2011/01/gays-game-of-thrones-series-george-martin After Elton blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''26 January 2011''': A number of actors in smaller roles in the production are revealed, including [[Mark Coney]] as [[Galbart Glover]] and [[Gerry O'Brien]] as [[Jonos Bracken]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Additional_Roles_Revealed/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 February 2011''': HBO release another behind-the-scenes video, this time focusing on Maisie Williams playing Arya Stark.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/1/31/the-artisans-maisie-williams.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 February 2011''': Margaret John, who played Old Nan, passes away at the age of 84, following a short illness.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-12342913 BBC News]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 February 2011''': It is reported that composer Stephen Warbeck has left the project. He has been replaced by [[Ramin Djawadi]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.tvsquad.com/2011/02/02/game-of-thrones/ TV Squad]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 February 2011''': International broadcasters are able to view the first two episodes of ''Game of Thrones'' at a screening in London. The reception is positive, with some caveats&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Remarks_from_International_Screening/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 February 2011''': HBO publishes an official pronunciation guide for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/2/11/official-pronunciation-guide-for-game-of-thrones.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 February 2011''': HBO host a special screening for cast and crew at a location in Soho, London. Again, the reception is very positive.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/02/thoughts-from-the-recent-screenings/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''19 February 2011''': HBO releases a video guide to some of the locations that will feature in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hbo.com/video/video.html?view=grid&amp;vid=1160821&amp;autoplay=true HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 February 2011''': British broadcaster Sky confirms that it will start showing ''Game of Thrones'' in the UK on its new Sky Atlantic channel on Monday 18 April 2011.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/April_18th_Premiere_in_the_UK/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''22 February 2011''': The blog posts the first picture of the three-eyed raven from the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/02/artists-cvs-reveal-info-about-vfx-work-include-first-image-of-three-eyed-crow/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''25 February 2011''': HBO report on the beginning of the '[[Maester's Path]]' marketing campaign, starting with a box of scrolls and scents to various bloggers, fansites and critics.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/2/25/scents-of-westeros-land-on-real-world-doorsteps.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 February 2011''': HBO release a new trailer for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/2/27/new-iron-throne-preview.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''28 February 2011''': HBO activate the 'Maester's Path' website and alternate-reality game.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.themaesterspath.com/#/intro The Maester's Path website]&lt;/ref&gt; Using clues gained from around the internet, players can solve puzzles to unlock rewards.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/The_Maesters_Path_Begins/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 March 2011''': George R.R. Martin announces 12 July 2011 as the publication date of the fifth novel in the series, ''A Dance with Dragons''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.georgerrmartin.com/if-update.html George R.R. Martin's website]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO release a new behind-the-scenes video about production design,&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/3/3/the-artisans-paul-inglis.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; featuring our first glimpse of the [[Red Keep]]. They also release a new, long trailer via ''Entertainment Weekly'' which features our first glimpse of [[the Wall]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/03/03/game-of-thrones-new-trailer/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''6 March 2011''': HBO reveals its April schedule, confirmation that the first episode of Season 1 will be called ''[[Winter is Coming (episode)|Winter is Coming]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hbo.com/index.html#/index.html/ HBO Schedules]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 March 2011''': HBO unlocks the second part of the Maester's Path.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/03/the-maesters-path-new-challenge/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 March 2011''': HBO releases the first official promotional poster for the series, depicting Sean Bean as Eddard Stark sitting on the Iron Throne, along with the Three-Eyed Crow.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/3/10/the-official-game-of-thrones-poster-is-here.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 March 2011''': HBO reveals that the second episode of Season 1 will be called ''[[The Kingsroad]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.spoilertv.com/2011/03/game-of-thrones-april-episode.html Spoiler TV]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 March 2011''': HBO releases a new trailer, 'Fear and Blood',&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/3/13/fear-and-blood-preview.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt; and a new featurette on House Stark.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2011/3/13/house-stark-feature.html HBO Production Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 March 2011''': Two new featurettes are released, one each on Houses Lannister and Baratheon.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Lannister_and_Baratheon_Feauterettes/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 April 2011''': HBO releases the episode titles up to Episode 7 of the first series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Episode_Titles_through_Episode_7/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''4 April 2011''': HBO schedule a special 15-minute preview of ''Game of Thrones'' to air at 9pm.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Sneak_Peek_on_April_3rd/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''8 April 2011''': Whilst Season 2 has not been confirmed, it is revealed that location scouting for the second season is proceeding in Croatia and Turkey. HBO confirm that the first season had a budget of $60 million.&lt;ref&gt;[http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052748703806304576244951109037560.html?mod=googlenews_wsj Wall Street Journal]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 April 2011''': HBO launches the ''Game of Thrones'' Viewer's Guide website, featuring character and house guides and an interactive map.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/#!/map/ HBO Viewer's Guide]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 April 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' starts airing on HBO to 4.2 million viewers on the first night. As a result of this success, HBO announces that the series has been renewed for a second season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/04/hbo-renews-game-of-thrones-for-second-season/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Season 2 pre-production==
* '''1 June 2011''': The first confirmed new filming location for [[Season 2]] is revealed: [[wikipedia:Ballintoy|Ballintoy Harbour]] in County Antrim.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.ballymoneytimes.co.uk/news/local/ballintoy_blockbuster_world_wide_smash_game_of_thrones_will_use_local_harbour_1_2732188 Ballymoney Times]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 June 2011''': HBO confirms that filming will return to Northern Ireland and the Paint Hall for Season 2.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/HBO_Confirms_Belfast_Filming/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 June 2011''': It is confirmed that Season 2 of the series will begin filming on 25 July.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.tvguide.com/News/Game-Thrones-Finale-Clarke-1034348.aspx TV Guide]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 June 2011''': It is confirmed that [[Natalie Dormer]] will be playing the role of [[Margaery Tyrell]], making her the first actor to be cast for the second season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/06/23/game-of-thrones-casting/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''24 June 2011''': Evidence mounts that [[wikipedia:Croatia|Croatia]] will be used as a filming location in Season 2.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/06/rumor-croatia-to-be-season-two-filming-location/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''4 July 2011''': Fan-favorite actor [[wikipedia:James Purefoy|James Purefoy]] states that he would be interested in a role on ''Game of Thrones'' if offered, and admits to being a fan of the books.&lt;ref&gt;[http://collider.com/james-purefoy-interview-ironclad-john-carter/97733/ Collider]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''8 July 2011''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Gwendoline Christie]] will be playing the role of [[Brienne]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/227044.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''14 July 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' gets no less than thirteen nominations for the 2011 Emmy Awards.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/07/game-of-thrones-garners-13-emmy-nominations/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''19 July 2011''': HBO confirms that [[Carice van Houten]] and [[Stephen Dillane]] have been cast in the roles of [[Melisandre]] and [[Stannis Baratheon]] respectively.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/07/19/stannis-melisandre/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt; George R.R. Martin also confirms that [[Oliver Ford Davies]] will be playing the role of Maester [[Cressen]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/229097.html?thread=14353129#t14353129 George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; Finally, it is announced the [[Liam Cunningham]] has been cast as [[Davos Seaworth]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/07/19/liam-cunningham-davos/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''23 July 2011''': It is confirmed that filming of Season 2 will take place in [[wikipedia:Iceland|Iceland]], particularly for Jon Snow's storyline. It is also confirmed that Jaime Lannister's Season 2 storyline will be expanded beyond what is in the second book, and that some elements of the third novel, ''A Storm of Swords'', will be brought up to the end of the second season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.accesshollywood.com/game-of-thrones-stars-and-creators-talk-upcoming-season-2-there-will-be-blood_article_51014 Access Hollywood]&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.Season 2 filming:
* '''25 July 2011''': Filming of Season 2 is due to start.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/07/season-two-filming-draws-near/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; The first scenes filmed include material at the Winterfell godswood with Kristian Nairn as Hodor.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/07/season-two-filming-begins-today/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''26 July 2011''': The second day of shooting for Season 2. A night scene at the Stark army camp involving Richard Madden is filmed, whilst another fan reports prepping for a scene involving Melisandre and some statues of the Seven, which will be shot later that week.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/page/2/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 July 2011''': David Benioff and D.B. Weiss confirm that the character of [[Asha Greyjoy]] will be renamed for the series. However, they decline to confirm rumors that [[Gemma Whelan]] has been cast in the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/07/producers-confirm-asha-name-change/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 July 2011''': HBO executives reassure fans that the series will run for as long as it needs to. However, they stress production limitations that mean that each season will remain 10 episodes long and that there could be further deviations from the books as the series continues.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/07/28/hbo-game-of-throne-cancel/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt; During an interview with Google, George R.R. Martin also highlights the show's budget limitations, pointing out that Robert's boar hunt in Season 1 suffered from such issues.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/28/george-r-r-martin-google-talk_n_912325.html Huffington Post]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 August 2011''': HBO officially confirm that Gemma Whelan will be playing the renamed [[Yara Greyjoy]] after months of rumors.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/08/02/game-of-thrones-greyjoy-asha/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt; They also confirm that [[Nonso Anozie]] will be playing [[Xaro Xhoan Daxos]] and that [[Kerr Logan]] will be playing [[Matthos Seaworth]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Meet_Xaro_Xhoan_Daxos/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 August 2011''': HBO officially confirm that [[Tom Wlaschiha]] is playing the role of [[Jaqen H'ghar]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/exclusive-tom-wlaschiha-is-jaqen-hghar/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 August 2011''': George R.R. Martin confirms that Roy Dotrice - who had to drop out of the role of Pycelle due to illness - has been recast as the role of [[Hallyne]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/231396.html?thread=14435300#t14435300 George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; ''Game of Thrones'' wins the 2011 [[wikipedia:TCA Award for Outstanding New Programe|TCA Award for Outstanding New Programe]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/friday-night-lights-game-thrones-220054 Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''8 August 2011''': HBO confirms that [[Hannah Murray]] has been cast as [[Gilly]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/5549/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; It is also confirmed that [[Karl Davies]] has been cast as a new character, [[Alton Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.accesshollywood.com/skins-uk-actress-and-former-british-soap-star-join-game-of-thrones-season-2_article_51810 Access Hollywood]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''9 August 2011''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Ben Crompton]] has been cast as [[Eddison Tollett]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/232992.html?thread=14481440#t14481440 George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; Filming for Season 2 on-set in the Paint Hall recommences.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/film-tv/news/cameras-roll-again-in-belfast-for-game-of-thrones-16035517.html Belfast Telegraph]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 August 2011''': It is revealed that [[Robert Pugh]] has been cast in the role of [[Craster]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/game-thrones-meet-craster-220687 Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt; and that [[Michael McElhatton]] will be playing the role of [[Roose Bolton]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/233352.html?thread=14494344#t14494344 George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 August 2011''': David Benioff confirms that shooting for Season 2 will span three countries: the previously-used Northern Ireland, the new location of Iceland and a third, undisclosed country.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/David_Benioff_on_Shooting_Locations/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; It is also revealed that actress [[Oona Chaplin]] has been cast in the series, but her role has not been revealed yet.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Oona_Chaplin_is/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 August 2011''': Hollywood actor [[wikipedia:Ron Perlman|Ron Perlman]] expresses a desire to work on ''Game of Thrones'', noting that he has worked previously with George R.R. Martin.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.accesshollywood.com/ron-perlman-would-love-to-reunite-with-beauty-and-the-beast-writer-george-rr-martin-for-game-of-thrones-role_article_52019 Access Hollywood]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 August 2011''': Oona Chaplin is reported as playing [[Jeyne Westerling]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.comicbookmovie.com/fansites/rorschachsrants/news/?a=44507 ComicBookMovie.com]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''18 August 2011''': Unofficial sources indicate that the third filming location for Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones'' will be [[wikipedia:Dubrovnik|Dubrovnik]] in [[wikipedia:Croatia|Croatia]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/filming-in-dubrovnik-croatia-becoming-a-reality/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''19 August 2011''': It is confirmed that actor [[Forbes KB]] has been cast as [[Lorren]], whilst director [[David Petrarca]] will be working on Season 2 of ''Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/The_Ironman_and_the_Director/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; It is also reported that German actress [[Laura Pradelska]] has been cast as [[Quaithe]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/unofficial-quaithe-and-lorren-cast-director-added/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''22 August 2011''': HBO formally confirm that Malta is out as a filming location for Season 2, whilst Croatia and Iceland have been brought in in addition to Northern Ireland.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Malta_Out_Croatia_and_Iceland_in_Says_HBO/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''24 August 2011''': The Maltese authorities confirm they are trying to clarify why the production did not return to Malta for filming of the second season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20110824/local/Dwejra-sand-fiasco-unrelated-to-Game-of-Thrones-move-to-Croatia.381585 Times of Malta]&lt;/ref&gt; [[Patrick Malahide]] is announced as having been cast as [[Balon Greyjoy]],&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/patrick-malahide-cast-as-balon-greyjoy/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; whilst [[Daniel Portman]] is announced in the role of [[Podrick Payne]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.accesshollywood.com/_article_52588 Access Hollywood]&lt;/ref&gt; and [[Ian Hanmore]] in the role of [[Pyat Pree]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/New_Casting_Pyat_Pree_and_Balon_Greyjoy/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''25 August 2011''': It is announced that [[Ralph Ineson]] has been cast as [[Dagmer|Dagmer Cleftjaw]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/one-more-ironborn-dagmer-cleftjaw-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; [[Lucian Msamati]] is also confirmed in the role of [[Salladhor Saan]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/08/25/game-of-thrones-pirate/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''28 August 2011''': It is revealed that [[Andy Beckwith]] has been cast in the role of [[Rorge]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/08/rorge-cast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 September 2011''': It is confirmed that [[Gerard Jordan]] has been cast in the role of [[Biter]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Rorge_and_Biter_Confirmed/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''6 September 2011''': [[Anthony Morris]] is confirmed in the role of the [[Tickler]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/236666.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 September 2011''': [[Steven Cole]] reveals he has been cast in a role for the second season, but does not clarify as which character.&lt;ref&gt;[https://twitter.com/#!/StevenCole_/status/110969103845556224 Steven Cole on Twitter]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 September 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' wins a [[wikipedia:Creative Arts Emmy Award|Creative Arts Emmy Award]] for [[title sequence|Main Title Design]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Game_of_Thrones_Take_Home_Emmy/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 September 2011''': HBO reveals several additional directors for the second season, including [[David Nutter]], [[Neil Marshall]] and [[Alik Sakharov]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/game-thrones-neil-marshall-season-234126 The Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt; It is also confirmed that [[Fintan McKeown]] has been cast as Ser [[Amory Lorch]], whilst rumors over Gregor Clegane's recasting continue to grow.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/09/amory-lorch-cast-gregor-recast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; In a later comment, Conan Stevens confirms that he has left the role of Gregor Clegane due to other projects.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/09/amory-lorch-cast-gregor-recast/#comment-131915 ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 September 2011''': High winds and rain caused by the arrival of [[wikipedia:Hurricane Katia|Hurricane Katia]] off the coast of Northern Ireland leads to a ''Game of Thrones'' catering tent collapsing, resulting in minor injuries.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/local-national/northern-ireland/five-injured-after-game-of-thrones-marquee-is-torn-up-by-katia-winds-16048996.html Belfast Telegraph]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 September 2011''': It is confirmed that Steven Cole is playing the role of [[Kovarro]], a new [[Dothraki]] character created especially for the TV series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Steven_Cole_is..._Kovarro/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''18 September 2011''': Peter Dinklage wins an Emmy Award for Best Supporting Actor for his role as Tyrion Lannister in ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Peter_Dinklage_Wins_Emmy/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; Filming in Dubrovnik, Croatia begins, with the city standing in for both King's Landing and Qarth. Andrew Wilde (Tobho Mott) and Dominic Carter (Janos Slynt) are both interviewed for Croatian TV.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/09/day-57-filming-in-dubrovnik-begins/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''22 September 2011''': [[Simon Fisher-Becker]] reveals that he is playing the role of the [[High Septon (Before the riot of King's Landing)|High Septon]] on the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.cultbox.co.uk/interviews/exclusives/1955-simon-fisher-becker-doctor-who-the-wedding-of-river-song-interview Cultbox]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''25 September 2011''': A very brief teaser trailer for Season 2 is released by HBO.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=frqB1snSYms&amp;feature=player_embedded YouTube]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''30 September 2011''': [[Tony Way]] is confirmed to be playing Ser [[Dontos Hollard]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Sansas_Own_Florian_Ser_Dontos_Hollard_Cast/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 October 2011''': [[Nicholas Blane]] is revealed to be playing a new character, the [[Spice King]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/10/day-75-casting-news-plus-more-set-photos-from-dubrovnik/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''10 October 2011''': [[Rose Leslie]] is confirmed in the role of [[Ygritte]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/10/10/game-of-thrones-rose-leslie/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 October 2011''': [[John Stahl]] is confirmed in the role of [[Rickard Karstark]], replacing [[Steven Blount]] from the first season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/243470.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; [[Simon Armstrong]] is also confirmed in the role of [[Qhorin Halfhand]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/243753.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 October 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' wins several awards at the 2011 [[wikipedia:Spike TV|Spike TV]] [[wikipedia:Scream Awards|Scream Awards]], including Best TV Show, Best Supporting Actor for Peter Dinklage and Breakout Female Performance for Emilia Clarke.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Game_of_Thrones_is_a_Scream/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 October 2011''': HBO Announces Game of Thrones Season One DVD and Blu-ray release date of March 30, 2012.&lt;ref&gt;[http://hbowatch.com/hbo-to-release-game-of-thrones-on-dvdblu-ray/ HBO Watch]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 October 2011''': It is confirmed that scenes beyond the Wall for the second season of ''Game of Thrones'' will be filmed on the [[wikipedia:VatnajĂśkull|VatnajĂśkull]] glacier in Iceland.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Iceland_Filming_Details_Revealed_Extras_Sought/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 November 2011''': [[Edward Dogliani]] is announced as having been cast in the role of [[Lord of Bones]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/249766.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''18 November 2011''': Filming in Northern Ireland for the second season is scheduled to wrap.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/More_from_Iceland/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 November 2011''': HBO airs the first behind-the-scenes preview of Season 2.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2011/11/season-two-in-production-video-airs-on-hbo/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''25 November 2011''': Filming in Iceland for Season 2 is scheduled to begin.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/More_from_Iceland/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''2 December 2011''': HBO releases a behind-the-scenes video for Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones'', focusing on the new look of Arya Stark in the second season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E5BrH30yE4c&amp;feature=player_embedded HBO's YouTube channel]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''4 December 2011''': In an interview, Charles Dance indicates that, if commissioned, Season 3 of ''Game of Thrones'' would begin shooting in May or June 2012.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bryanreesman.com/blog/2011/12/04/charles-dance-talks-neverland-underworld-awakening-and-game-of-thrones/ Bryan Reesman's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; ''Game of Thrones'' is referenced on ''[[wikipedia:The Ten-Per-Cent Solution|The Ten-Per-Cent Solution]]'', an episode of ''[[wikipedia:The Simpsons|The Simpsons]]'', alongside several other HBO shows.&lt;ref&gt;[http://hbowatch.com/the-simpsons-parody-hbo-game-of-thrones/ HBOWatch]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 December 2011''': HBO releases a new trailer for Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Latest_Game_of_Thrones_Teaser/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''12 December 2011''': Filming of Season 2 is scheduled to wrap.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/More_from_Iceland/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Post-Season 2 filming period==
* '''14 December 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' is nominated for Outstanding Performance by a Stunt Ensembly and Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble at the [[wikipedia:Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild Awards]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/SAG_Awards_Honor_Game_of_Thrones/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 December 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' is nominated for two awards at the 2012 [[wikipedia:Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe Awards]], for Best Drama Series and Best Supporting Actor for Peter Dinklage.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/12/15/golden-globe-nominations/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''16 December 2011''': ''Game of Thrones'' is named the second-most-pirated TV show of 2011.&lt;ref&gt;[http://torrentfreak.com/top-10-most-pirated-tv-shows-of-2011-111216/ TorrentFreak]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''7 January 2012''': Westeros.org is able to confirm the line-up of directors for Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Probable_Director_Breakdown/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''13 January 2012''': HBO confirms that the second season of ''Game of Thrones'' will start airing on 1 April 2012.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Season_2_Premiere_Date_Set_April_1st/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''15 January 2012''': Peter Dinklage wins the Best Supporting Actor Award at the [[wikipedia:Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe Awards]] for his work on ''Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Peter_Dinklage_Takes_Home_a_Globe/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''17 January 2012''': The Location Guide website runs a feature on the Icelandic shooting for Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones''. The feature reveals that 200 crewmembers and 12 horses were used for shooting, and due to the short hours of daylight a lot of prep-work was done in the dark.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.thelocationguide.com/blog/2012/01/game-of-thrones-films-frozen-landscapes-on-location-in-iceland-for-second-season/ The Location Guide]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''29 January 2012''': HBO release a longer trailer for Season 2.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Season_2_Trailer/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''30 January 2012''': Figures released by HBO reveal that ''Game of Thrones'' has leapfrogged ''Boardwalk Empire'' to become the third-most-popular series in HBO's history, behind only ''True Blood'' and ''The Sopranos''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winteriscoming.net/2012/01/thrones-now-2nd-most-watched-show-on-hbo-3rd-most-in-networks-history/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 February 2012''': It is reported that co-producer Vince Gerardis has said that the Battle of the Blackwater will take up a full quarter of the [[Blackwater (episode)|episode of the same name]] and that HBO have plans to adapt the ''Dunk &lt;nowiki&gt;'n'&lt;/nowiki&gt; Egg'' short stories. However, this is due to mistranslation and is later amended to mean that HBO are looking at different options for those stories.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Blackwater_the_Hedge_Knight_and_More/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''14 February 2012''': HBO releases a new behind-the-scenes video focusing on the use of Iceland as a filming location, and the practical problems of filming with only four hours of daylight a day.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Making_Game_of_Thrones_Iceland/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''21 February 2012''': HBO releases a new behind-the-scenes video entitled invitation to the set.&lt;ref&gt;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones - Season 2 Invitation to the Set]]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''22 February 2012''': [[Carice van Houten]] discussed her role in an interview with Cyril Falisse from the Ferryman Critical. She mentioned plans to film a third season in summer 2012.&lt;ref&gt;http://lepasseurcritique.blogspot.com/2012/02/interview-carice-van-houten.html&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''24 February 2012''': HBO releases a new trailed entitled &quot;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones Season 2:|Power and Grace]]&quot; through their HBO Go service. The trailer is released generally on 26 February 2012.&lt;ref&gt;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones Season 2:|&quot;Power and Grace&quot; trailer]]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''3 March 2012''': HBO and Entertainment Weekly release a new trailer entitled &quot;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones Season 2 Seven Devils Trailer|Seven Devils]]&quot;, notable for including a licensed soundtrack, the song 'Seven Devils' by British group [[wikipedia:Florence and the Machine|Florence and the Machine]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/03/03/game-of-thrones-seven-devils/ Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''4 March 2012''': The ''[[wikipedia:The Simpsons|Simpsons]]'' episode ''Exit Through the Kwik-E-Mart'' airs, featuring a homage to the ''Game of Thrones'' title sequence.&lt;ref&gt;[http://io9.com/5890410/watch-the-simpsons-game-of-thrones-intro io9.com]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''5 March 2012''': Season 1 of ''Game of Thrones'' is released on DVD and Blu-ray. On release, the DVD and Blu-ray become the fastest-selling release in the history of HBO. It also sets new HBO records for digital sales on [[wikipedia:iTunes|iTunes]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Game_of_Thrones_Registers_Big_DVD_Sales/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;

* '''10 March 2012''': HBO airs a new trailer entitled &quot;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones Season 2 The More You Love Trailer|The More You Love]]&quot; before the premiere of their film ''Game Change''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winteriscoming.net/2012/03/new-trailer-the-more-you-love-airs-on-hbo/ article about &quot;The More You Love&quot; trailer]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''11 March 2012''': HBO airs a production featurette entitled &quot;[[:Video:Game Of Thrones Season 2 Daenerys Targaryen Character Profile|Daenerys Targaryen Character Profile]]&quot; before an airing of the film ''How to Train Your Dragon''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winteriscoming.net/2012/03/new-character-profile-video-for-daenerys/  article about the Daenerys Targaryen Character Profile featurette]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''1 April 2012''': Season 2 of ''Game of Thrones'' begins airing on HBO.
* '''10 April 2012''': HBO officially commissions a third season of ''Game of Thrones''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/04/10/game-of-thrones-renewed-3/?ew_packageID=20470532 Entertainment Weekly]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Season 3 pre-production==
* '''1 June 2012''': It is revealed, via [http://twitter.com/#!/kerrywerryberry Twitter], that [[Kerry Ingram]] is going to play [[Shireen Baratheon]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.spoilertv.com/2012/06/game-of-thrones-season-3-shireen.html?utm_source=dlvr.it&amp;utm_medium=tumblr Spoiler Tv.com]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''22 June 2012''': It is announced that Season 3 of ''Game of Thrones'' will be partially filmed in Morocco.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.nsnews.com/entertainment/movie-guide/Cinematographer+eyes+Irish+project/6823119/story.html North Shore News]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''27 June 2012''': HBO confirmed that Daniel Minahan, Alik Sakharov and David Nutter will be returning to direct episodes in the third season, as well as the news that producers David Benioff and D.B. Weiss will also co-direct. [[Alex Graves]] and [[Michelle MacLaren]] are confirmed as joining the directing roster for the season.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Season_3_Directors/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''28 June 2012''': [[Charlotte Hope]] is confirmed in the role of [[Myranda]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://wicnet.tumblr.com/post/26084130142/charlotte-hope-joins-the-cast WiC.net Tumblr]&lt;/ref&gt;
* '''30 June 2012''': [[Clive Russell]] is confirmed in the role of Ser [[Brynden Tully]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winteriscoming.net/2012/06/clive-russell-cast-as-the-blackfish/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.Pilot filming:
*'''24 October 2009''': Day 1 of pilot production. Work begins at [[wikipedia:Doune Castle|Doune Castle]] in Scotland, which is standing in for [[Winterfell]]. Set and costume rehearsals seem to be taking place rather than filming.&lt;ref&gt;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/tayside_and_central/8322843.stm BBC News]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/filming-at-doune-castle/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''26 October 2009''': Day 3 of pilot production. Filming begins. The Winterfell feast is the first scene shot.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/day-3-filming-at-doune-castle/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; The German band [[wikipedia:Corvus Corax|Corvus Corax]] appear as a troupe of musicians performing at the feast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php?s=&amp;showtopic=39506&amp;view=findpost&amp;p=1955739 Westeros.org forums]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''27 October 2009''': Day 4 of pilot production. The main cast wraps up shooting at Doune Castle.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/day-4-filming-at-doune-castle/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''28 October 2009''': Day 5 of pilot production. No filming as the production relocates to Belfast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/day-5-no-filming-today/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/117909.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; Robert Stromberg, fresh from working on [[wikipedia:James Cameron|James Cameron]]'s film ''[[wikipedia:Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', is confirmed to be working on visual effects for the pilot.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/award-winning-vfx-supervisor-working-on-pilot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''29 October 2009''': Day 6 of pilot production. The prologue scene is filmed at [[wikipedia:Tollymore Forest Park|Tollymore Forest Park]] with extensive fake snow used.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/10/day-6-filming-the-prologue/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''2 November 2009''': Day 10 of pilot production. The scenes where [[Eddard]] executes [[Gared]] and [[Robb]] and [[Jon]] find the [[direwolves]] in the snow, are filmed at [[wikipedia:Cairncastle|Cairncastle]], [[wikipedia:County Antrim|County Antrim]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-11-filming-rolls-on-updated/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.towerofthehand.com/essays/hbo/pilot_locations_gallery.html Tower of the Hand]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''3 November 2009''': Day 11 of pilot production. George R.R. Martin signs copies of his books in a Belfast book store and is joined by many cast members who mingle and talk with fans into the evening.&lt;ref&gt;[http://thewertzone.blogspot.com/2009/11/belfast-report-01.html The Wertzone]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://thewertzone.blogspot.com/2009/11/signing-pictures.html The Wertzone]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://thewertzone.blogspot.com/2009/11/belfast-report-02.html The Wertzone]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/reports-from-grrm-signing/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/reports-from-the-grrm-moot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/3608/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; There are indications that the new scene between [[Ros]], [[Tyrion]] and [[Jaime]] in a [[King's Landing]] [[Pleasure house|brothel]] was also filmed on this day.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-11-filming-rolls-on-updated/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''4 November 2009''': Day 12 of production. The scene in Winterfell courtyard where [[Tommen]] and [[Bran]] are sparring is filmed.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-13-filming-something/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/118374.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''5 November 2009''': Day 13 of production. Filming takes place at [[wikipedia:Castle Ward|Castle Ward]], [[wikipedia:County Down|County Down]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/3624/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; The scene being shot is most likely [[King Robert]]'s arrival at Winterfell, due to the presence of an effects-enhanced carriage that will be turned into Cersei's wheelhouse.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-17-more-filming/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''10 November 2009''': Day 18 of production. Filming has been underway for the last few days at the [[Paint Hall]] in Belfast. The famous, &quot;The things I do for love,&quot; scene is apparently shot on this day.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-18-final-days-of-uk-filming/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''11 November 2009''': Day 19 of production. It is reported that filming of Season 1 will be spread over 30 weeks, if the series goes ahead.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/3637/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''12 November 2009''': Day 20 of production. Filming in Northern Ireland is concluded and the production moves to Morocco.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/day-21-filming-in-morocco/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''13 November 2009''': Day 21 of production. Filming in Morocco gets underway at the [[wikipedia:Ouarzazate|Ouarzazate]] studio.
*'''16 November 2009''': Day 24 of production. George R.R. Martin reports arriving at the studio and that the filming of the first meeting between Khal [[Drogo]] and [[Daenerys]] has already taken place. The wedding scene is filmed that night.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/118848.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''18 November 2009''': Day 26 of production. Principle photography of the pilot is concluded.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/11/thats-a-wrap/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''19 November 2009''': The pilot wrap party is held.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/120749.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Post-pilot period==
*'''1 December 2009''': It is revealed that [[wikipedia:Jamie Bamber|Jamie Bamber]] auditioned for the role of Jaime Lannister but did not get the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/12/news-and-notes/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''15 December 2009''': Irish actor [[wikipedia:Peter O'Meara|Peter O'Meara]] expresses an interest in auditioning for the series, if picked up.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/12/irish-actor-peter-omeara-hints-at-possible-casting/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''17 December 2009''': HBO trademarks the ''Game of Thrones'' name for merchandising purposes.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2009/12/hbo-files-for-game-of-thrones-trademark/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''14 January 2010''': HBO's progamming chief Michael Lombardo gives a very positive and enthusiastic report on the pilot's production and on the dailies seen so far.&lt;ref&gt;[http://livefeed.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/01/hbo-games-of-thrones-dailies-look-fantastic.html The Hollywood Reporter Live Feed]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''15 January 2010''': The wolf pups used to stand in for the dirwolf pups on the pilot are put up for sale.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/01/for-sale-one-direwolf-pup/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; HBO are rumored to be planning to book two of the Paint Hall's four filming sets for the next five years.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/01/rumor-hbo-looking-to-book-paint-hall-for-5-years/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''24 February 2010''': American actress [[wikipedia:Felicia Day|Felicia Day]] expresses an interest in auditioning for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://geekadelphia.com/2010/02/24/farpoint-2010-a-conversation-with-felicia-day/ Geekadelphia]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''27 February 2010''': A source claims that HBO has begun contracting services in Belfast that will be needed to work on the pilot, including making payments.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/02/rumor-hbo-gearing-up-for-filming/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''2 March 2010''': HBO officially picks up ''Game of Thrones'' for a 10-episode first season (including the pilot).&lt;ref&gt;[http://livefeed.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/03/hbo-greenlights-game-of-thrones-.html The Hollywood Reporter Live Feed]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/03/game-of-thrones-hbo-george-rr-martin-.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://tunedin.blogs.time.com/2010/03/03/hbo-picks-up-thrones-places-bet-on-dustin-hoffman/#more-8711 TIME Magazine]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.aintitcool.com/node/44136 Ain't It Cool News]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/136965.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/137285.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/03/hbo-officially-picks-up-game-of-thrones/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;

==Season 1 pre-production==
*'''3 March 2010''': The Northern Ireland government discloses that the TV project could bring as much as ÂŁ20 million to the local economy.&lt;ref&gt;[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/northern_ireland/8547516.stm BBC News]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''10 March 2010''': [[Bryan Cogman]] is revealed to be writing Episode 4 of the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/03/new-crew-members/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''13 March 2010''': An extensive call for crewmembers for ''Game of Thrones'' goes out.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/03/call-for-crew-members-goes-out/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''16 March 2010''': [[Jane Espenson]] is added to the writing roster. She will be writing Episode 6 of the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/03/game-of-thrones-hbo.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''19 March 2010''': It is announced that Jennifer Ehle has left the ''Game of Thrones'' project. Her role as Catelyn Stark will now be played by Northern Irish actress [[Michelle Fairley]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://livefeed.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/03/catelyn-stark-recast-in-game-of-thrones.html The Hollywood Reporter Live Feed]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/142143.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''24 March 2010''': It is confirmed that George R.R. Martin will be writing Episode 8 of Season 1. The remaining episodes (1-3, 5, 7 and 9-10) will be written by producers David Benioff and D.B. Weiss.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/03/grrm-on-recasting-catelyn-and-writing-his-script/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''25 March 2010''': Rumors begin circulating that Tamzin Merchant is also departing the project.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/03/dany-the-next-to-be-recast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''2 April 2010''': [[wikipedia:Elena Satine|Elena Satine]] is reported as having auditioned for the role of Daenerys, strengthening rumors of Merchant's departure.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/04/production-busy-looking-for-actors-and-crew/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''8 April 2010''': Maisie Williams releases pictures of herself wielding a replica of Arya's sword, [[Needle]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://web.archive.org/web/20100412022957/http://grrm.livejournal.com/146489.html/ George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.valyriansteel.com/2010/04/08/maisie-williams-as-arya/ Valyrian Steel]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''9 April 2010''': George R.R. Martin comments on how overseas viewers will be able to watch the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/146855.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''12 April 2010''': HBO issues a press release confirming that they have hired [[David J. Peterson]] of the [[wikipedia:Language Creation Society|Language Creation Society]] to create a fully-working [[Dothraki]] language that will be used in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bscreview.com/2010/04/hbos-a-game-of-thrones-time-to-learn-dothraki/ BSC Review]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/148593.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''18 April 2010''': George R.R. Martin expands on some of the challenges facing the project and on what will be happening in his episode.&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/42396-grrm-in-chicago/page__view__findpost__p__2114409 Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/42396-grrm-in-chicago/page__view__findpost__p__2113906 Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/04/qa-session-at-the-c2e2-con/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''27 April 2010''': Releases an image of an extra in costume.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/04/photo-costumed-extra/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''29 April 2010''': It is confirmed that Tamzin Merchant has left the project and her role of Daenerys is being recast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/04/game-of-thrones-george-r-r-martin.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''1 May 2010''': George R.R. Martin completes his script and goes on to report that Ros may return in later episodes and that the TV series will be very faithful, but deviations from the books are possible and more likely the longer it goes on.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/151109.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/05/grrm-hands-in-script/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''21 May 2010''': It is confirmed that [[Emilia Clarke]] has replaced Tamzin Merchant in the role of Daenerys.&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/05/game-of-thrones-hbo.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/153995.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''25 May 2010''': The Televisionary blog reports it has secured a copy of the pilot and that the quality of the finished episode is very high.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/05/televisionary-blown-away-by-pilot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.televisionaryblog.com/2010/05/channel-surfing-glee-gets-third-season.html Televisionary Blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''27 May 2010''': The UK's tallest man, [[wikipedia:Neil Fingleton|Neil Fingleton]], reports that he has auditioned for the role of Gregor Clegane in the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/05/uks-tallest-man-auditions-for-gregor/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''3 June 2010''': HBO shows an internal trailer of the series to investors, apparently to a positive reception. Fans begin clamouring for a trailer of some kind to be released publicly.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/hbo-shows-thrones-trailer-at-investor-meeting/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''5 June 2010''': Director [[wikipedia:Brian Kirk|Brian Kirk]] joins the project and will direct two episodes of Season 1.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/possible-new-director-revealed/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''13 June 2010''': HBO airs a 22-second teaser [[trailer]] for ''Game of Thrones'' ahead of the third season premiere of ''[[wiki:True Blood|True Blood]]'', to a mostly positive reception.&lt;ref&gt;[http://hbo.vo.llnwd.net/o32/av/progressive/series/game-of-thrones/winter-is-coming-329901-1-hi.mov Game of Thrones teaser trailer]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/hbo-airs-game-of-thrones-teaser-trailer/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/156324.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''19 June 2010''': [[Finn Jones]] is cast as [[Loras Tyrell]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/loras-cast-grrm-confirms-and-promises-more/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/157386.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/liverpool-news/local-news/2010/06/23/former-hollyoaks-actor-finn-jones-is-cast-in-hbo-s-a-game-of-thrones-tv-series-starring-sean-bean-100252-26705338/ Liverpool Echo]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''23 June 2010''': [[Kristian Nairn]] is cast as [[Hodor]]&lt;ref&gt;[https://twitter.com/Kristiannairn/statuses/16816803489 ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/kristian-nairn-is-hodor/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; and [[Roy Dotrice]] as Grand Maester [[Pycelle]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/158167.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/roy-dotrice-is-grand-maester-pycelle/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/158167.html]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''24 June 2010''': It is reported that HBO are going to be building a massive castle set at the [[wikipedia:Magheramorne|Magheramorne]] quarry in Northern Ireland for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.larnetimes.co.uk/news/Extras-needed-for-new-TV.6382643.jp The Larne Times]&lt;/ref&gt; Martin later confirms that the set for [[Castle Black]] will be built on this site, including a fully-operable winch elevator as described in the books.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/158683.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''25 June 2010''': Martin confirms that [[Paul Engelen]] has been hired to work on hair and make-up for the series.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/158909.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/06/2083/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''6 July 2010''': It is announced that [[John Bradley-West]] has been cast as [[Samwell Tarly]],&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.mmu.ac.uk/news/articles/1296/ Manchester Metropolitan University News]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/we-have-a-sam/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/161485.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; [[Luke McEwan]] as [[Rast]] and [[Miltos Yerolemou]] as [[Syrio Forel]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/more-casting-news-syrio-and-rast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/161789.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''7 July 2010''': Westeros.org confirms that [[Conan Stevens]] has been cast in the role of [[Gregor Clegane]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/The_Mountain_That_Rides_Cast/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/conan-stevens-to-play-gregor/ ]&lt;/ref&gt; Casting sources indicate that the prologue scene will be reshot and the role of [[Will]] will be recast due to [[Bronson Webb]]'s other commitments.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/will-being-recast-prologue-will-be-reshot/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''8 July 2010''': At a book signing in San Diego, George R.R. Martin reveals that the actor [[wikipedia:Richard Griffiths|Richard Griffiths]] was approached for the role of Illyrio but in the end a deal could not be reached. He also revealed that an exceptional actress is in negotiations for another role and, if cast, may even affect how he writes the character in future books.&lt;ref&gt;[http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/topic/44396-grrm-in-san-diego/page__view__findpost__p__2183838 Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''10 July 2010''': It is confirmed through Twitter that [[Jamie Sives]] has been cast as [[Jory Cassel]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Jamie_Sives_Cast_as_Jory_Cassel/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/jamie-sives-is-jory-cassel/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/162195.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; Lena Headey answers fan questions about her casting as Cersei Lannister and how she will approach the role.&lt;ref&gt;[http://imaginemeandyouthemovie.com/publicity/qalena_july2010.html Imagine Me &amp; You Fansite]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''12 July 2010''': It is confirmed through Twitter that [[Ian McElhinney]] has been cast as Ser [[Barristan Selmy]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Barristan_the_Bold_Cast/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/barristan-the-bold-on-board/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/162910.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; The Hollywood Reporter later announces that [[Aidan Gillen]], a fan-favorite choice for the role, has been cast as Lord [[Petyr Baelish|Petyr 'Littlefinger' Baelish]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://livefeed.hollywoodreporter.com/2010/07/game-of-thrones-casts-wire-veteran.html The Hollywood Reporter]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/aidan-gillen-is-littlefinger/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/Aidan_Gillen_IS_Littlefinger/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/161982.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''14 July 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms on his blog that amongst the Stark guardsmen, only Jory will have a speaking role. The others will be extras.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/162195.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''15 July 2010''': It is announced that [[Conleth Hill]] has been cast in the role of [[Varys]] and that Jamie Campbell Bower has left the project as Ser Waymar Royce, to be replaced for the pilot reshoots by [[Rob Ostlere]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2010/07/game-of-thrones-casting-news.html The Chicago Tribune]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''16 July 2010''': No less than twenty new casting announcements are made by HBO, including [[Jerome Flynn]] as [[Bronn]] and [[James Cosmo]] as [[Jeor Mormont]]. It is also confirmed that the role of Gared has been recast.&lt;ref&gt;[http://thewertzone.blogspot.com/2010/07/soldier-bronn-and-trojan-mormont.html The Wertzone]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://thewertzone.blogspot.com/2010/07/ton-of-supporting-actors-for-thrones.html The Wertzone]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/164794.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/164389.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; It is also confirmed that the production will not be returning to Morocco. Instead, Daenerys's scenes will be filmed in Malta, using some of the castles left behind by the Knights Hospitaller. [[Daniel Minahan]] and [[Alan Taylor]] are announced as additional episode directors for the series itself.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/164794.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''17 July 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Natalia Tena]] has been cast as [[Osha]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/165235.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''18 July 2010''': Miltos Yerolemou, who plays Syrio Forel, confirms that he has been receiving stage fight choreography lessons from famous fight choreographer [[wikipedia:William Hobbs (choreographer)|William Hobbs]] on a one-to-one basis (Hobbs is not officially attached to the ''Game of Thrones'' series).&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/syrios-dance-master/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''21 July 2010''': A number of cast members convene in Belfast for costume fittings, a script read-through and general pre-production work. The Castle Black set is under construction by this time.&lt;ref&gt;[http://winter-is-coming.net/2010/07/thrones-cast-heads-to-belfast/ ]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''22 July 2010''': George R.R. Martin confirms that [[Brynden Tully|Brynden]], [[Hoster Tully|Hoster]] and [[Edmure Tully]] will not debut until the second season due to cast budgetary constraints. He suggests that Brynden's story functions in Season 1 will instead be fulfilled by Ser Vardis Egen and Ser Rodrik Cassel.&lt;ref&gt;[http://grrm.livejournal.com/166493.html George R.R. Martin's blog]&lt;/ref&gt;

sections.Season 5 filming:
* '''25 July 2014''': At San Diego Comic Con, HBO confirmed 9 new cast members: &lt;ref&gt;[http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/07/25/game-of-thrones-season-5-cast]/&lt;/ref&gt;
** [[Alexander Siddig]] as Prince [[Doran Martell]]
** [[DeObia Oparei]] as [[Areo Hotah]]
** [[Toby Sebastian]] as Prince [[Trystane Martell]]
** [[Nell Tiger Free]] as Princess [[Myrcella Baratheon]]
** [[Keisha Castle-Hughes]] as [[Obara Sand]]
** [[Jessica Henwick]] as [[Nymeria Sand]]
** [[Rosabell Laurenti Sellers]] as [[Tyene Sand]]
** [[Enzo Cilenti]] as [[Yezzan zo Qaggaz]]
** [[Jonathan Pryce]] as the [[High Sparrow]]
* '''30 July 2014''': [[Liam Cunningham]], [[Carice van Houten]], [[Sophie Turner]], [[Daniel Portman]], [[Gwendoline Christie]], [[Finn Jones]], and [[Kristian Nairn]] arrive in Belfast, Northern Ireland to began filming [[Season 5]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://watchersonthewall.com/cast-sightings-in-belfast-ramp-up-and-a-baby-brought-in-as-game-of-thrones-season-five-filming-continues/#more-763]&lt;/ref&gt;
